channel.title: Cannot get sdwdate to sync
channel.description:
I am pretty excited about this project and was eager to try it out.
This is what I have going on, Debian 11 installed on a laptop with a WWAN modem as its primary connection to the web. Kicksecure installed ok for me, no major issues other than having to switch from Gnome to xfce(side note, is using xfce even necessary for kicksecure's security if a DE is being used)?
I seem to be having some trouble getting sdwdate to connect, with it failing every address almost instantly. I have some experience with sdwdate from qubes but that was mainly when the time was not syncd on the host. I do not think this is the case here as I have a good enough time sync for apt-transport-tor, tor-browser, and a vpn
I can connect to tor and update the repos over the debian and kicksecure onion v3 addresses so to some extent the time is sync'd enough for tor to work so sdwdate should work.

item.title: Cannot get sdwdate to sync
item.dc:creator: secondone2post
item.description:
I am pretty excited about this project and was eager to try it out.

This is what I have going on, Debian 11 installed on a laptop with a WWAN modem as its primary connection to the web.
Kicksecure installed ok for me, no major issues other than having to switch from Gnome to xfce(side note, is using xfce even necessary for kicksecure’s security if a DE is being used)?

I seem to be having some trouble getting sdwdate to connect, with it failing every address almost instantly. I have some experience with sdwdate from qubes but that was mainly when the time was not syncd on the host. I do not think this is the case here as I have a good enough time sync for apt-transport-tor, tor-browser, and a vpn

I can connect to tor and update the repos over the debian and kicksecure onion v3 addresses so to some extent the time is sync’d enough for tor to work so sdwdate should work.
